                    <!-- SDP TAB -->
                    <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="sdp" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="sdp-tab">
                        <h4>Software Development Project (SDP)</h4>
                        <p>
                            SDP focuses on <span class="highlight">end-to-end software development</span>
                            using real-world engineering practices. Students work in teams, follow 
                            software engineering life cycle models, and implement complete applications.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Applies concepts from <b>OOP, DBMS, OS, Networks, and SE</b> in one integrated project.</li>
                            <li>Promotes <b>team collaboration, version control, testing, and documentation</b>.</li>
                            <li>Bridges gap between <b>academic learning</b> and <b>industry-grade software projects</b>.</li>
                            <li>Helps build portfolio projects for <b>internships and placements</b>.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="mt-2">
                            <span class="tag">Team Work</span>
                            <span class="tag">SDLC</span>
                            <span class="tag">Industry Exposure</span>
                            <span class="tag">Git / Tools</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- EDI TAB -->
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="edi" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="edi-tab">
                        <h4>Engineering Design & Innovation (EDI)</h4>
                        <p>
                            EDI encourages students to identify <span class="highlight">real-life problems</span> 
                            and propose innovative engineering solutions. It focuses on creativity, prototyping and
                            practical design skills.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Promotes <b>problem identification</b> from society, industry, or campus needs.</li>
                            <li>Includes <b>rapid prototyping, modelling, and testing</b> of innovative ideas.</li>
                            <li>Improves <b>interdisciplinary thinking</b> by combining concepts from multiple domains.</li>
                            <li>Prepares students for <b>hackathons, innovation contests, and startup ideas</b>.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="mt-2">
                            <span class="tag">Innovation</span>
                            <span class="tag">Prototyping</span>
                            <span class="tag">Societal Impact</span>
                            <span class="tag">Interdisciplinary</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- DT TAB -->
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="dt" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="dt-tab">
                        <h4>Design Thinking (DT)</h4>
                        <p>
                            Design Thinking at VIT trains students to approach problems with a 
                            <span class="highlight">user-centric mindset</span>, moving through stages like 
                            Empathize, Define, Ideate, Prototype, and Test.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Teaches how to <b>understand users</b> and their pain points thoroughly.</li>
                            <li>Encourages <b>brainstorming and creative idea generation</b> without bias.</li>
                            <li>Supports <b>iterative prototyping</b> and feedback-driven improvements.</li>
                            <li>Useful in <b>product design, UX/UI, service design, and entrepreneurship</b>.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="mt-2">
                            <span class="tag">User-Centric</span>
                            <span class="tag">Empathy</span>
                            <span class="tag">Ideation</span>
                            <span class="tag">Prototype & Test</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- COURSE PROJECTS TAB -->
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="course-project" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="cp-tab">
                        <h4>Course Projects</h4>
                        <p>
                            Course projects are embedded within regular subjects and help students 
                            <span class="highlight">apply theoretical concepts</span> in a focused mini-project format.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Reinforces learning from <b>core and elective courses</b>.</li>
                            <li>Encourages <b>hands-on practice</b> alongside lectures and labs.</li>
                            <li>Helps students explore <b>specific topics in depth</b> within a course.</li>
                            <li>Acts as a foundation for <b>larger capstone projects, SDP, or research work</b>.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="mt-2">
                            <span class="tag">Concept Application</span>
                            <span class="tag">Mini Projects</span>
                            <span class="tag">Continuous Learning</span>
                            <span class="tag">Skill Building</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

